Reasoning: The paper focuses on the human and social aspects of eLearning systems, which suggests that it may fall under the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the reuse of learning materials, which could fall under the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. The classification of sustainability requirements into five dimensions (individual, social, technical, environmental, and economic) suggests that the paper may also fall under the Cybernetics (cs.CY) and Civil Engineering (cs.CE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the development of a framework for sustainable eLearning systems, which could fall under the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
